\begin_layout Section
Compute Gamma
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
File (Matlab script): ComputeGamma.m
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Matlab script description
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
This matlab script mainly implement and estimate the following two equations,
 (21) and Appendix (D.7) (Freestone et al.
 2011 NeuroImage).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Field, v(r), is decomposed of a finite-dimensional state vector and a vector
 of Gaussian basis functions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Define 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma=\int_{\Omega}\phi(r)\phi^{T}(r)dr$
\end_inset

.
 Firstly, programmatically define 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(r)$
\end_inset

, as a vector of Gaussian basis functions.
 Each Gaussian function is defined as 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(r-r')=e^{(-\frac{(r-r')^{T}(r-r')}{\sigma_{\phi}^{2}})}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

